headline: UK PM condemns 'death to the IDF' chants at Glastonbury Festival
description: British punk-rap group Bob Vylan led crowds to chant, 'Death, death to the IDF,' a reference to the acronym for the Israeli military, during their set on Saturday at the world-famous UK music festival. The Israeli embassy said in a statement that it was 'deeply disturbed by the inflammatory and hateful rhetoric expressed on stage.'

headline: In France, workplaces confront resurgence in machoism
description: Everyday sexism is persisting among employees and companies continue to perpetuate values tied to male dominance. Yet, company leadership has not embraced the clear shift toward diversity policies that some of their American counterparts have taken.

headline: 'Why are audiences, especially young people, willing to pay up to €610 to see Beyoncé?'
description: As ticket prices for music festivals and star-studded concerts continue to skyrocket, spectators appear less worried about the cost of admission than about whether they can secure a ticket at all, writes Le Monde's Michel Guerrin in his column.

headline: Serge Hefez, psychiatrist: 'Our children are too alone in front of screens'
description: The teenager who stabbed a school supervisor in eastern France in June had no history of mental health problems and later showed no remorse. Psychoanalyst Serge Hefez draws a link between the growing lack of empathy he has observed in his patients and their ever-increasing screen time.
